long_desc.thetext:
qxWeb example:

    q.ready(function() {
      q(document.body).on("pointerdown", function(e) {});
      q(document.documentElement).on("pointerdown", function(e) {});
    });

When executed in IE11 using document mode 10, moving the mouse will cause "Stack overflow" and "Out of stack space" exceptions. This is because the._onPointerEvent method of the documentElement's PointerCore is called both for the browser's native MSPointer* events (as expected) and for synthetic pointer* events generated by the body element's PointerCore, even though it's only attached to MSPointer* events.
